" For Vim, copy it to
"     for Unix and OS/2:  ~/.vimrc
"  for MS-DOS and Win32:  $VIM\_vimrc
"
" For NeoVim
" - Use `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/nvim/init.vim` instead of `.vimrc` for your |config|.
" - Use `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/nvim` instead of `.vim` to store configuration files.
"
" help :h 'setting'
" check :set xxx?
" reverse :set xxx!
